-- Google Says Fewer Than 3% of German Households Opted Out of `Street View'
-- B y   J a n n   B e t t i n g a
-- 2010-10-21T04:01:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-21/google-says-2-89-of-german-households-opt-out-of-street-view-.html
Google Inc.  said that 2.89 percent
of households in Germany’s 20 biggest cities asked the Internet-
search provider not to show their properties in the company’s
Street View mapping service.  Google received requests from 244,237 of the roughly 8.46
million households in the cities, the U.S. company’s German unit
in Hamburg said in an e-mailed statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Jann Bettinga  in Frankfurt at 
 jbettinga@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Frank Connelly at   fconnelly@bloomberg.net . 